nextLexeme

public java.lang.String nextLexeme(java.lang.String delims,
                                   boolean consumeDelim)
Get next lexeme in string being interpret()'ed using the delimiter set passed in the 'delims' argument, with the option of consuming the delimiter. NOTE that this is only useful for non-blank delims, since it presumes a blank will be left over at the front of the string. class StringTokenizer in Java 1.1.7 and before is not a full-bodied lexing facility.
Parameters:
delims -  
consumeDelim -  
Returns:
